12. What will be the output of the following code and if it is wrong then
what will be thecorrect code?
begin
fork begin
initial
for (bit[2:0] i=0;i<=3;i++)
$display($time,”value of i=%0d”,i);
end
begin
#1
;
$display(“Executed 2nd begin block”);
end
join
$display(“Fork Join Ended”);
end

answer:
initial begin
  fork
  begin
 integer i;
for (i = 0; i <= 3; i = i + 1)
 $display($time, " value of i=%0d", i);
  end 
begin
#1;
$display($time, " Executed 2nd begin block");
 end
join
$display($time, " Fork Join Ended");
end
